{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17633339","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17633339"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T17:51:43+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T17:51:43+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17470"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"17470","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/17470"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10160"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"70771"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10160","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10160"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17470"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"56237"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"5326"},{"type":"tags","id":"5526"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"23760"},{"type":"contributions","id":"23797"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"70771","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/70771"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EResearch demonstrates strong links between access to family planning services and socioeconomic development. Studies from multiple countries show that women with access to contraception are more likely to complete their education and maintain employment.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the primary relationship between contraceptive access and social development?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Contraceptive access enables educational and economic participation","Contraceptive access reduces maternal mortality and morbidity","Contraceptive access improves child health outcomes","Contraceptive access strengthens family stability","Contraceptive access enhances gender equality in healthcare"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EEvidence shows that \u003Cstrong\u003Econtraceptive access enables educational and economic participation\u003C/strong\u003E by allowing women to plan their families and pursue opportunities. This has far-reaching benefits for social and economic development.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EContraceptive access reduces maternal mortality and morbidity\u003C/strong\u003E - While this is an important benefit, it is secondary to the broader social and economic impact\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EContraceptive access improves child health outcomes\u003C/strong\u003E - Though child health may improve with planned pregnancies, this is not the primary social development benefit\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EContraceptive access strengthens family stability\u003C/strong\u003E - While family planning can support stable families, the key benefit is individual empowerment\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EContraceptive access enhances gender equality in healthcare\u003C/strong\u003E - Though contraception contributes to healthcare equality, its main impact is on educational and economic opportunity\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EResearch consistently demonstrates that access to voluntary family planning is a key factor in reducing poverty and achieving development goals through improved educational and economic opportunities for women.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Access to contraception is a key factor in improving educational and economic outcomes for women and girls.","Contraceptive access helps reduce maternal mortality by preventing unintended pregnancies and unsafe abortions.","Family planning enables women to complete their education and participate more fully in the workforce."],"references":["Famjikly planning/contraceptive methods. World Health Organisation. Updated September 5, 2023. Available from: https://www.who.int/news-room/fact-sheets/detail/family-planning-contraception"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"56237"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17470"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"56237","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/56237"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-16T13:54:53+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-16T13:56:03+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10160"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"70771"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"